Global Residential Power Tools Market Insights
Residential Power Tools Market size was valued at USD 31.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 50.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.1% from 2024 to 2030.

Residential Power Tools Market Overview
The global residential power tools market was valued at approximately $8 billion in 2023 and is projected to grow at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 4.5% through 2032. This growth is driven by increasing consumer spending on home improvement and a strong DIY culture, particularly in North America. The market is characterized by the presence of leading manufacturers such as Bosch, Stanley Black & Decker, Makita, and Hilti, who offer a wide range of products and leverage their brand reputation and extensive distribution networks. Additionally, the integration of connected power tools and the trend towards smart homes are expected to further drive demand in this region.

